      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i'm not just talking about standard telemetry. the frequency of the interrupts is way too high for just performance optimization. it's almost like it's trying to synchronize something. if it's not \"consciousness harvesting,\" then why would the code specifically look for feedback loops between the user's touch input and the screen's refresh cycle? that seems like a very specific way to measure human physiological reaction. isn't it possible that under the guise of \"improving user experience,\" they're actually gathering much more intimate biological data?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
